class="block-intro-text"><p>A domain name refers to a website address or URL that people use to find businesses and other entities on the internet. A URL typically starts with a protocol identifier (https://), followed by the name of the website and the domain suffix (.com). If you want to know how to register a domain name, read through our guide below.</p></div></div></div></div><div
class="section-content"><div
class="container"><div
class="narrow-container"><div
