<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-domain-name-800x800-2020087.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=250&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="250" height="250" alt="How to Register a Domain Name:">
</picture></div><p>A domain name should be registered with a domain name registrar, such as Namecheap. You can choose to purchase just a domain name, or one with web hosting from your service provider. Most web hosting packages come with a free domain name. Follow our step-by-step guide to register a domain name.</p></div><div
id="how-to-register-a-domain-name-section1" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>1.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=check-if-your-domain-name-is-available>Check if your domain name is available.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-register-a-domain-name-section1-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=perform-a-domain-name-search>Perform a domain name search.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-perform-a-domain-name-search-on-google-domains-288x288-2020087.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Perform a domain name search."></div></div><p>Before you settle on a domain name for your business, you will need to conduct a search to see if it is available. You can use <a
href="https://domains.squarespace.com/">Squarespace Domains</a> to search existing business names by typing your domain name into the search bar.</p><p>A list of results will pop up showing you a list of available and unavailable suffixes with their URLs. It will also tell you the cost to purchase any available URLs.</p><p>You can also check domain name availability on <a
href="https://www.namesnack.com/">NameSnack</a>.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Make sure that your domain name is easy to pronounce, describes your business concept, and is not longer than 14 characters.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-register-a-domain-name-section2" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>2.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=find-an-icann-accredited-registrar>Find an ICANN-accredited registrar.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-register-a-domain-name-section2-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-a-suitable-registrar>Choose a suitable registrar.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-choose-a-suitable-registrar-288x288-2020087.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose a suitable registrar."></div></div><p>ICANN, which stands for Internet Corporation for Assigned Names and Numbers, is an official organization that regulates the domain name market.</p><p>Although unapproved registrars can sell domain names, it is safer to register your domain name with an accredited provider.</p><p>You can find a list of current ICANN-accredited registrars on their <a
href="https://www.icann.org/en/accredited-registrars">website</a>.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-register-a-domain-name-section3" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>3.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=go-to-your-chosen-registrar-039-s-website>Go to your chosen registrar&#039;s website.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-register-a-domain-name-section3-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=register-your-domain-name>Register your domain name.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-register-your-domain-name-288x288-2020087.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Register your domain name."></div></div><p>On the "domains" page, type in your domain name in the search bar, and click search.</p><p>A note stating whether your domain is available will pop up, along with a list of alternatives.</p><p>On the check out page, you'll likely be given the option to purchase a hosting package or professional email address along with your domain name.</p><p>Type in your billing and payment information, and pay for the domain.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-register-a-domain-name-section3-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=purchase-an-existing-domain-name>Purchase an existing domain name (if applicable).</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
